This End User License Agreement ("Agreement") is a binding legal contract between you (either an individual or an entity) and the developer of NovaSurvey. By downloading, accessing, or using the Software, you agree to be bound by the terms of this Agreement.

---

### 1. License Grant and Tiers
The Software is distributed under a Dual-License model. Your usage rights depend on your classification and license tier:

#### A. Educational and Individual Use (Free Tier)
If you are an individual researcher, a student, or an academic professional using the Software strictly for educational, academic, or personal research purposes, you are granted a revocable, non-exclusive, non-transferable, and free license to use the Software.

#### B. Free Trial Mode (Evaluation)
If you are a commercial entity, government agency, or organization evaluating the Software without a Commercial License Key, you are granted a limited evaluation license. Under this tier, the Software's processing engine is strictly limited to a maximum of 10,000 rows per execution. Attempting to bypass, reverse engineer, or modify this technical limitation is a material breach of this Agreement.

#### C. Enterprise and Commercial Use (Paid Tier)
Any use of the Software for commercial purposes, internal corporate operations, government official statistics, or processing datasets exceeding the 10,000-row evaluation limit requires a valid Commercial Enterprise License. Enterprise Licenses are cryptographically signed and must be actively maintained.

